                            <comment id="12659845" author="apurtell" created="Tue, 30 Dec 2008 16:44:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch passes all local tests.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12659971" author="stack" created="Tue, 30 Dec 2008 22:43:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;d wonder if we should add this what with it not being atomic?  Should it take a row lock?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Should method be called exists rather than testRow?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12659972" author="stack" created="Tue, 30 Dec 2008 22:44:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Otherwise, patch looks good&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12660006" author="apurtell" created="Wed, 31 Dec 2008 02:20:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Since you want it called &apos;exists&apos; I guess it needs to be the swiss army knife that implies.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12660054" author="apurtell" created="Wed, 31 Dec 2008 09:53:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is a low impact change so I went ahead and committed it based on feedback from the review of the earlier patch. Can revert if it is problematic.&lt;/p&gt;

